text: Sabri Freddy Khattab (; born 12 January 1990) is an Egyptian footballer who plays as a midfielder for OBOS-ligaen side Elverum. ==Club career== Sabri signed for FC Edmonton from hometown side Kvik Halden in 2017. He made his debut in a 1–0 loss to Jacksonville Armada, coming on as a substitute for Dean Shiels. In July 2017, Sabri returned to Norway and signed for Elverumhttp://www.elverumfotball.no/nyheter/sabri-khattab-klar-for-elverum ==International career== Although he was born in Norway, Sabri declared himself for the Egyptian national team in 2013, however he has yet to be called up. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:People from Halden Category:Egyptian footballers Category:Norwegian footballers Category:Norwegian people of Egyptian descent Category:Association football midfielders Category:Kvik Halden FK players Category:Bryne FK players Category:FC Edmonton players Category:Norwegian First Division players Category:North American Soccer League players Category:Egyptian expatriate footballers Category:Norwegian expatriate footballers Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in Canada Category:Egyptian expatriate sportspeople in Canada Category:Expatriate soccer players in Canada
